WorkItem.ClosedComment: This looks fixed in today's bits.
WorkItem.Description:
Compiling this snippet with the latest compiler in the develop branch:

```
var blah: any[];
blah.splice(0, 1)[0].dispose();

```
Results in:

error TS2094: Could not find dotted name 'dispose'.

The type is already "any" so the existence of the dispose member should not be type checked.
WorkItem.Summary: Type check should not be applied to any[] array
